2026-03-14T18:33:00 [user-prompt] {"timestamp":"2026-03-15T00:33:00.346Z","hook_event_name":"UserPromptSubmit","session_id":"55d512ef-f5a8-4f2f-ab73-40f89c960886","transcript_path":"/Users/possum/Library/Application Support/Code/User/workspaceStorage/45d4d075d8cc3a456e89b76d1fa86ac6/GitHub.copilot-chat/transcripts/55d512ef-f5a8-4f2f-ab73-40f89c960886.jsonl","prompt":"it isn't, it wants to do this\n\nReview your DNS records\nRecords we found:\n\n0\n\nOur scan may have missed uncommon records or custom subdomains. Compare the list below to your current DNS provider (most likely your registrar) and add any missing records. Pay close attention to all records on the zone apex, records of the type A, AAAA, and CNAME and records needed for email like MX, SPF, DMARC, DKIM, and MTA-STS.\n\nTo receive email at @tend.cx addresses, add a mail exchange (MX) record.\n\nAn A, AAAA or CNAME record for the www subdomain is required for the tend.cx subdomain to resolve.\n\nAn A, AAAA or CNAME record pointing to the root domain is required for the tend.cx domain to resolve.\n\nYour traffic is almost ready to proxy\n\nHow proxying works\nYour DNS records tell Cloudflare where your web content is hosted, so we can hide the origin and proxy your web traffic.\n\n\nProxied: HTTP traffic goes through the Cloudflare network. Required for services like caching, smart routing, and Web Application Firewall.\n\n\n\nDNS only: HTTP traffic bypasses Cloudflare and goes directly to the origin, but DNS resolution still benefits from our fast and secure network. A gray cloud means proxying is off, no cloud means the record is not eligible for proxying.\n\n\nDNS management for tend.cx\n\nAbout DNS records\nDNS Setup: Full\n\n\nImport DNS Records\nSearch DNS Records\nYour search yielded 0 results\n\nType\n\nName\n\nContent\n\nProxy status\n\nTTL\n\nActions\nNo DNS records. Add a DNS record individually or import a BIND file above.\n\n","cwd":"/Users/possum/Projects/tend/tend-cli"}
