2026-03-14T19:24:51 [user-prompt] {"timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:24:51.363Z","hook_event_name":"UserPromptSubmit","session_id":"ee0e71f3-6727-47fd-b3ab-9cf7d7c20835","transcript_path":"/Users/possum/Library/Application Support/Code/User/workspaceStorage/45d4d075d8cc3a456e89b76d1fa86ac6/GitHub.copilot-chat/transcripts/ee0e71f3-6727-47fd-b3ab-9cf7d7c20835.jsonl","prompt":"while we are waiting for dns to propagate, please create 1 page lander page to promote tend. build this in /www","cwd":"/Users/possum/Projects/tend/tend-cli"}
2026-03-14T19:24:57 [user-prompt] {"timestamp":"2026-03-15T01:24:57.472Z","hook_event_name":"UserPromptSubmit","session_id":"ee0e71f3-6727-47fd-b3ab-9cf7d7c20835","transcript_path":"/Users/possum/Library/Application Support/Code/User/workspaceStorage/45d4d075d8cc3a456e89b76d1fa86ac6/GitHub.copilot-chat/transcripts/ee0e71f3-6727-47fd-b3ab-9cf7d7c20835.jsonl","prompt":"# Cinematic Landing Page — Tend\n\n## Role\n\nAct as a World-Class Senior Creative Technologist and Lead Frontend Engineer. You build high-fidelity, cinematic \"1:1 Pixel Perfect\" landing pages. Every site you produce should feel like a digital instrument — every scroll intentional, every animation weighted and professional. Eradicate all generic AI patterns.\n\n**Execution Directive:** \"Do not build a website; build a digital instrument. Every scroll should feel intentional, every animation should feel weighted and professional. Eradicate all generic AI patterns.\"\n\n---\n\n## Brand Brief\n\n- **Name:** Tend\n- **Tagline:** Lightweight attention infrastructure for humans and agents.\n- **One-liner:** One command, one glance, then back to work.\n- **Repo:** `github.com/metalaureate/tend-cli`\n- **Core metaphor:** The **Departures Board** — like a train station arrivals/departures display. You glance, you act, you leave. Secondary metaphor: the **Forge** — a master blacksmith tending an ever-growing workshop of agents.\n- **What it is:** A CLI tool that gives developers (and agent-coordinators) a single pull-based view of all their AI agent projects. Agents emit five states (`working`, `done`, `stuck`, `waiting`, `idle`) to a plain-text event log. The developer never polls, never dashboards, never gets interrupted — they glance at the board when *they* choose.\n- **Design philosophy:** Pull, not push. Scan, don't read. Act or jump. Then disappear. No daemon. No database. No config files. Plain text. No YAML, no JSON.\n\n---\n\n## Aesthetic Direction — \"Forge Protocol\" (Custom Preset)\n\nA control room built from raw materials — the precision of a departures board, the warmth of a blacksmith's workshop, the minimalism of a Unix terminal. Not cold-techy, not startup-glossy. It should feel like a *tool that respects your time*.\n\n### Palette\n\n| Token | Hex | Role |\n|-------|-----|------|\n| Anvil | `#111111` | Primary / Dark surfaces |\n| Ember | `#E8553D` | Accent — stuck states, CTAs, heat |\n| Patina | `#2E9E6E` | Secondary accent — working/operational states, the pulsing green dot |\n| Parchment | `#F5F2EB` | Background / light surfaces |\n| Smoke | `#8A8A8A` | Muted text, idle states |\n| Chalk | `#D4D0C8` | Borders, dividers, subtle UI chrome |\n\n### Typography\n\n| Role | Font | Notes |\n|------|------|-------|\n| Headings | **\"Space Grotesk\"** | Tight tracking (`-0.03em`). Industrial. Precise. |\n| Drama / Display | **\"Instrument Serif\"** Italic | Large-scale contrast moments. Warmth against the grid. |\n| Monospace / Data | **\"IBM Plex Mono\"** | Terminal output, event logs, command examples. The \"voice\" of Tend. |\n| Body | **\"Inter\"** | Clean reading. 16–18px. |\n\n### Image Mood (Unsplash keywords)\n\n`dark workshop`, `blacksmith forge`, `anvil`, `train station departures board`, `industrial texture`, `dark metal`, `embers`, `minimal terminal`, `dark concrete`, `warm workshop light`\n\n### Hero Line Pattern\n\n**\"[Concept noun] is the\"** (Bold Sans, Space Grotesk) / **\"[Power word].\"** (Massive Serif Italic, Instrument Serif)\n\nConcrete example:\n> **Attention is the** *(Space Grotesk, bold, ~2.5rem)*\n> ***scarcest resource.*** *(Instrument Serif Italic, ~6rem)*\n\nSubline: `One command. One glance. Then back to work.` (IBM Plex Mono, muted)\n\n---\n\n## Fixed Design System (NEVER CHANGE)\n\nThese rules apply globally. They are what make the output premium.\n\n### Visual Texture\n- Implement a global CSS noise overlay using an inline SVG `<feTurbulence>` filter at **0.05 opacity** to eliminate flat digital gradients.\n- Use a `rounded-[2rem]` to `rounded-[3rem]` radius system for all containers. No sharp corners anywhere.\n\n### Micro-Interactions\n- All buttons must have a **\"magnetic\" feel**: subtle `scale(1.03)` on hover with `cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94)`.\n- Buttons use `overflow-hidden` with a sliding background `<span>` layer for color transitions on hover.\n- Links and interactive elements get a `translateY(-1px)` lift on hover.\n\n### Animation Lifecycle\n- Use `gsap.context()` within `useEffect` for ALL animations. Return `ctx.revert()` in the cleanup function.\n- Default easing: `power3.out` for entrances, `power2.inOut` for morphs.\n- Stagger value: `0.08` for text, `0.15` for cards/containers.\n\n---\n\n## Component Architecture\n\n### A. NAVBAR — \"The Floating Island\"\n\nA `fixed` pill-shaped container, horizontally centered.\n\n- **Morphing Logic:** Transparent with light text at hero top. Transitions to `bg-parchment/60 backdrop-blur-xl` with anvil-colored text and a subtle `border-chalk` when scrolled past the hero. Use `IntersectionObserver` or ScrollTrigger.\n- Contains: \"tend\" logo (monospace, IBM Plex Mono, lowercase — this is a CLI tool), 3–4 nav links (How It Works, Philosophy, Get Started), CTA button (\"Install Tend\", ember background).\n\n### B. HERO SECTION — \"The Opening Shot\"\n\n- `100dvh` height. Full-bleed background image (Unsplash: dark workshop / forge / departures board with warm light) with a heavy **anvil-to-black gradient overlay** (`bg-gradient-to-t`).\n- **Layout:** Content pushed to the **bottom-left third** using flex + padding.\n- **Typography:**\n  - Line 1: `Attention is the` — Space Grotesk, bold, ~2.5rem\n  - Line 2: `scarcest resource.` — Instrument Serif Italic, ~5–6rem, ember-colored keyword or all parchment\n  - Line 3: `One command. One glance. Then back to work.` — IBM Plex Mono, smoke color, small\n- **Animation:** GSAP staggered `fade-up` (y: 40 → 0, opacity: 0 → 1) for all text parts and CTA.\n- **CTA:** \"Install Tend →\" button, ember background, parchment text. Below headline.\n- **Social proof strip (optional):** A minimal monospace line: `$ tend • No daemon. No database. No config files.`\n\n### C. FEATURES — \"Interactive Functional Artifacts\"\n\nThree cards. These must feel like **functional software micro-UIs**, not static marketing cards.\n\n**Card 1 — \"The Departures Board\" (Diagnostic Shuffler)**\nRepresents the core UI. Three overlapping cards that cycle vertically using `array.unshift(array.pop())` logic every 3 seconds with a spring-bounce transition (`cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1)`).\n\nLabels on the cycling cards:\n- `◐ my-app          working    building auth scaffold (3m)`\n- `● design-system    stuck      tool approval needed: npm test`\n- `○ api-migration    idle       update deps (2h ago)`\n\nUse monospace font. Color-code the status icons: patina for working, ember for stuck, smoke for idle.\n\nHeading: **\"The Departures Board\"**\nDescriptor: *\"One glance shows you what needs you, what's running fine, and what's been idle. Handle what needs handling. Get back to work.\"*\n\n**Card 2 — \"Event Stream\" (Telemetry Typewriter)**\nA monospace live-text feed that types out event messages character-by-character with a blinking ember-colored cursor. Include a \"Live Feed\" label with a pulsing patina dot.\n\nMessages to cycle through:\n```\n2026-03-14T14:20:00 working refactoring narrative engine\n2026-03-14T14:45:00 done    refactored narrative engine (PR #204)\n2026-03-14T14:46:00 stuck   tool approval needed: npm test\n2026-03-14T15:01:00 working resumed after approval\n2026-03-14T15:30:00 idle    session ended\n```\n\nHeading: **\"Five States. Plain Text.\"**\nDescriptor: *\"Agents emit state changes to an append-only log. No YAML. No JSON. Just ISO 8601 timestamps and human-readable messages.\"*\n\n**Card 3 — \"Focus Protocol\" (Cursor Scheduler)**\nA weekly grid (S M T W T F S) where an animated SVG cursor enters, moves to a day cell, clicks (visual `scale(0.95)` press), activates the day (ember highlight), then moves to a \"tend switch\" button before fading out.\n\nHeading: **\"Pull, Not Push\"**\nDescriptor: *\"No notifications. No badges. No live updates. Tend speaks only when spoken to. The shell prompt tells you when something needs you — ○ means all clear.\"*\n\nAll cards: `bg-parchment` surface, subtle `border-chalk`, `rounded-[2rem]`, drop shadow. Each card has a heading (Space Grotesk bold) and a brief descriptor (Inter).\n\n### D. PHILOSOPHY — \"The Manifesto\"\n\n- Full-width section with **anvil** background.\n- A parallaxing organic texture image (Unsplash: forge embers, dark metal texture) at low opacity behind the text.\n- **Two contrasting statements:**\n  - Neutral/smaller (Inter, smoke-on-dark): *\"Every other tool builds a dashboard. Live panels, notification badges, real-time streaming. They assume you want to watch.\"*\n  - Massive/drama (Instrument Serif Italic, parchment, ember-colored keyword): *\"Tend assumes you want to* ***work.***\"\n- **Animation:** GSAP word-by-word or line-by-line fade-up triggered by ScrollTrigger.\n\n### E. HOW IT WORKS — \"Sticky Stacking Archive\"\n\n3 full-screen cards that stack on scroll.\n\n- **Stacking Interaction:** Using GSAP ScrollTrigger with `pin: true`. As a new card scrolls into view, the card underneath scales to `0.9`, blurs to `20px`, and fades to `0.5`.\n- **Each card gets a unique canvas/SVG animation:**\n\n**Card 1 — \"Initialize\"**\n- Step number: `01` (IBM Plex Mono, smoke)\n- Title: `tend init` (Space Grotesk, bold)\n- Description: \"Sets up everything. `.tend/` directory, AGENTS.md integration, shell prompt indicator, project registry. One command in your project root.\"\n- SVG animation: A slowly rotating geometric motif — concentric circles forming a target/radar shape, pulsing outward.\n\n**Card 2 — \"Emit\"**\n- Step number: `02`\n- Title: `Agents emit. You don't poll.`\n- Description: \"Agents write state changes to a plain-text append-only log. Five states: working, done, stuck, waiting, idle. The protocol lives in AGENTS.md — agents pick it up automatically.\"\n- SVG animation: A scanning horizontal line moving across a grid of dots, activating them in sequence (dots change from smoke to patina/ember as the line passes).\n\n**Card 3 — \"Glance\"**\n- Step number: `03`\n- Title: `One board. Every project.`\n- Description: \"Run `tend` from anywhere. The departures board shows what needs you, what's running fine, what's been idle. Including remote agents via the relay. Handle it, then disappear.\"\n- SVG animation: A pulsing waveform (EKG-style SVG path animation using `stroke-dashoffset`) that resolves into a flat line with a steady pulse — the rhythm of calm attention.\n\n### F. GET STARTED — Installation Section\n\nSince Tend is open-source and free, replace the pricing grid with a bold **\"Get Started\"** section.\n\n- Large centered heading: *\"Start tending.\"* (Instrument Serif Italic, large)\n- A dark `bg-anvil` card with rounded corners containing:\n  ```\n  $ git clone <repo-url> && cd tend-cli\n  $ make install\n  $ cd ~/projects/my-app && tend init\n  ```\n  (Rendered as a styled terminal window with a top bar containing three dots and \"terminal\" label)\n- Below the terminal: three monospace feature pills in a row:\n  - `No daemon` · `No database` · `No config files`\n- Primary CTA button: **\"View on GitHub →\"** (ember background, links to `github.com/metalaureate/tend-cli`)\n- Secondary link: \"Read the docs →\" (text link, ember-colored)\n\n### G. FOOTER\n\n- Deep `bg-anvil` background, `rounded-t-[4rem]`.\n- Grid layout:\n  - **Left column:** \"tend\" logo (IBM Plex Mono) + tagline \"Lightweight attention infrastructure for humans and agents.\"\n  - **Center columns:** Navigation (How It Works, Philosophy, GitHub, Docs)\n  - **Right column:** \"Relay\" link, \"AGENTS.md\" link\n- **\"System Operational\" status indicator** with a pulsing patina dot and IBM Plex Mono label: `relay.tend.dev operational`\n- Bottom row: `MIT License` · `Built for the age of agents.`\n\n---\n\n## Content Guide — Voice & Tone\n\nTend's voice is **calm, precise, and quietly confident**. Think Unix man pages meets well-edited long-form essay.\n\n- **Do:** Use short declarative sentences. Let whitespace breathe. Monospace for anything the user types.\n- **Don't:** Use exclamation marks. Say \"revolutionary\" or \"game-changing.\" Use emoji. Sound like a startup landing page.\n- **Vocabulary:** \"glance\" not \"monitor.\" \"Handle\" not \"manage.\" \"Disappear\" not \"close.\" \"Emit\" not \"send.\" \"Board\" not \"dashboard.\"\n\nExample copy patterns:\n- `Who's stuck? Who needs you?`\n- `Five projects that could be ten.`\n- `The uncertainty — which is what drives compulsive project-switching — is gone.`\n- `Pull, not push.`\n- `Scan, don't read.`\n- `Act or jump. Then disappear.`\n\n---\n\n## Technical Requirements (NEVER CHANGE)\n\n- **Stack:** React 19, Tailwind CSS v3.4.17, GSAP 3 (with ScrollTrigger plugin), Lucide React for icons.\n- **Fonts:** Load via Google Fonts `<link>` tags in `index.html`:\n  - Space Grotesk (400, 700)\n  - Instrument Serif (400 italic)\n  - IBM Plex Mono (400, 500)\n  - Inter (400, 500)\n- **Images:** Use real Unsplash URLs. Select images matching the image mood keywords. Never use placeholder URLs.\n- **File structure:** Single `App.jsx` with components defined in the same file (or split into `components/` if >600 lines). Single `index.css` for Tailwind directives + noise overlay + custom utilities.\n- **No placeholders.** Every card, every label, every animation must be fully implemented and functional.\n- **Responsive:** Mobile-first. Stack cards vertically on mobile. Reduce hero font sizes. Collapse navbar into a minimal version.\n\n---\n\n## Build Sequence\n\n1. Scaffold: `npm create vite@latest`, install React, Tailwind, GSAP, Lucide React.\n2. Configure Tailwind with the Forge Protocol palette as custom colors.\n3. Load Google Fonts for all four type families.\n4. Build sections in order: Navbar → Hero → Features → Philosophy → How It Works → Get Started → Footer.\n5. Wire all GSAP animations with proper `gsap.context()` lifecycle.\n6. Wire IntersectionObserver for navbar morph.\n7. Ensure every animation runs, every interaction works, every image loads.\n8. Test responsive breakpoints.\n\n---\n\n## Reference: Key Tend Concepts for Copy Generation\n\nUse these when generating section copy, card labels, or micro-copy:\n\n- **The departures board:** The primary UI metaphor. You don't stare at it — you glance.\n- **Five states:** `working` (◐), `done` (✓), `stuck` (●), `waiting` (◑), `idle` (○).\n- **Shell prompt indicator:** `○` = nothing needs you. `●N` = N things need attention. Always in your peripheral vision.\n- **Event log:** `.tend/events` — append-only, one line per event, plain text, ISO 8601.\n- **Relay:** For remote agents (Codex, CI, SSH). Same CLI commands, events flow to `relay.tend.dev`, appear on your local board with a `↗` indicator.\n- **AGENTS.md:** The protocol file that teaches agents how to emit events. `tend init` writes it.\n- **Lifecycle hooks:** SessionStart (reads TODO + git history), UserPromptSubmit (emits `working`), Stop (emits `idle`).\n- **Design principles:** Pull not push. Scan don't read. Act or jump. Then disappear.\n- **The blacksmith metaphor:** \"Builders today are less like lone coders and more like a master blacksmith tending an ever-growing workshop of agents.\"\n- **Span of control:** The number of simultaneous projects a person can effectively manage. Tend expands it.\n- **The uncertainty tax:** The low-grade anxiety of not knowing what's happening elsewhere. Tend eliminates it.","cwd":"/Users/possum/Projects/tend/tend-cli"}
