2026-03-15T07:02:13 [user-prompt] {"timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:02:13.718Z","hook_event_name":"UserPromptSubmit","session_id":"49f76a63-735b-4798-aff6-4d89a4c11f5b","transcript_path":"/Users/possum/Library/Application Support/Code/User/workspaceStorage/45d4d075d8cc3a456e89b76d1fa86ac6/GitHub.copilot-chat/transcripts/49f76a63-735b-4798-aff6-4d89a4c11f5b.jsonl","prompt":"i don't think it works. see here, that project\n\n% tend init    ○\n✓ AGENTS.md already has tend integration in product-discovery\n✓ Initialized .tend/ in product-discovery\n\nbut the agents.md is:\n\n# Agents\n\nThis project uses markdown files as AI agent definitions. Each `.md` file in the project root contains a system prompt that Copilot follows when invoked.\n\n## Orchestrator\n\n### Pipeline Runner — `pipeline-runner.md`\nThe main entry point. Orchestrates the full product discovery pipeline from trend scan to final brief.\n- **Invoke**: \"Run the research pipeline for [idea]\" or \"@pipeline-runner\" or \"What should we build?\"\n- **Output**: Complete research folder with all reports + `idea_brief_[slug].md` (includes Team Summary)\n- **Two phases**: Concept Generation (Stages -1.0 through -1.4) → Concept Validation (Stages 0 through 5)\n- **Universal on-ramp**: Stage 0 (Screening) accepts ideas from any source — trend pipeline, shower thoughts, conversations\n- **Key feature**: All outputs scoped to `research/YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS_slug/` for worktree isolation\n- **Team Summary**: Every `idea_brief_[slug].md` ends with a 7-field shareable summary (pitch, what exists, growth mechanic, execution, retention mechanic, 48hr milestone, first marketing message)\n- **First Marketing Message**: The \"first marketing message\" field in Team Summary is crafted using `frameworks/viral-hooks.yaml` — the evaluator spawns a subagent to match the idea to viral domains/archetypes and generate candidates\n\n## Pipeline Agents\n\nThese agents run in sequence during a research pipeline run.\n\n### Stage -1.3: Blue Ocean Transform\nApplies Blue Ocean Strategy's Four Actions Framework to reconstruct the value curve of trend-generated concepts. Most concepts from trend ideation land in red oceans (obvious applications of current technology). The transform preserves the demand signal but creates differentiated positioning.\n- **Input**: Selected concepts from trend ideation (or any red ocean concept)\n- **Output**: Updated `pitches/auto/YYYYMMDD.md` with Four Actions tables, noncustomer analysis, transformed concepts\n- **Method**: For each concept: (1) identify the red ocean, (2) Eliminate/Reduce/Raise/Create, (3) identify 3 tiers of noncustomers, (4) rewrite concept with new value curve\n- **On-ramp**: Skip if concept is already differentiated\n- **Off-ramp**: Keep original framing if transform doesn't improve it\n\n### Stage -1.4: Product Pitch\nCaptures each concept advancing to validation as a structured pitch in `pitches/[slug].md`.\n- **Input**: Transformed (or original) concept\n- **Output**: `pitches/[slug].md` covering problem, insight, mechanics, target user, timing, competitive position, unit economics, kill criteria\n- **On-ramp**: Enter here with any idea from any source — the universal entry point for concepts that bypass the trend pipeline\n- **Gate**: If the pitch falls apart when written up concretely, rework or kill before screening\n\n### Stage 0: Screening — `screener.md`\nScores an idea against `criteria.yaml` + `frameworks/retention.yaml` before committing to research. Also generates search keywords.\n- **Input**: An idea (one or two sentences) + criteria YAML + retention framework YAML\n- **Output**: `research/YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS_slug/00_screening.md` (includes search keywords for intel-gather)\n- **Key behavior**: Distribution & Growth and Retention & Stickiness are each weighted 1.5x. Scores each criterion 0 / 0.5 / 1. Outputs 5-7 pain-based keyword phrases (not solution jargon).\n\n### Stage 0.5: Intel Gathering — `intel-gather.mjs`\nAutomated data collection script (not an LLM agent). Gathers live data from social platforms.\n- **Input**: Idea string + optional `--keywords` + optional `--output` + optional flags (`--1w`, `--48h`, `--skip-xpoz`)\n- **Output**: `[output_dir]/*.json` + `[output_dir]/digest/*.md` (Twitter, Reddit, Instagram, TikTok, Brave, HN data)\n- **Dependencies**: `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` (via `xpoz-mcp.mjs` wrapper), Brave API key, HN Algolia (free)\n- **Required**: `XPOZ_API_KEY` must be set in `.env` (fails otherwise). Use `--skip-xpoz` to bypass (not recommended for quality research).\n- **Usage**: `node intel-gather.mjs \"your idea\" --keywords=\"kw1,kw2,kw3\" --output=\"research/[folder]/raw\"`\n- **Keywords**: Each keyword phrase gets its own full set of Twitter/Reddit/TikTok/HN queries. Brave queries use the full idea string (run once). If omitted, key terms are auto-extracted.\n- **Digest**: After collection, generates 6 compact markdown digests (`raw/digest/twitter.md`, `reddit.md`, `instagram.md`, `tiktok.md`, `hn.md`, `brave.md`) that strip metadata bloat and deduplicate. Research agents read these instead of parsing 70+ JSON files.\n- **XPOZ MCP**: Uses `xpoz-mcp.mjs` — a direct MCP client that talks to `https://mcp.xpoz.ai/mcp`. Replaces the `@xpoz/xpoz` SDK. TikTok collection is wired up and activates automatically when XPOZ enables TikTok tools on their server.\n\n### Stage 1a: Twitter Research — `twitter-researcher.md`\nScours Twitter/X for builders, competitors, sentiment, and market signals.\n- **Data source**: Reads `[research_folder]/raw/digest/twitter.md` first, falls back to training knowledge\n- **Output**: `[research_folder]/01_twitter_research.md`\n- **Key sections**: Builders & Competitors, Sentiment, Pain Points, Retention Signals, Signal Strength\n\n### Stage 1b: Reddit Research — `reddit-researcher.md`\nDeep-dives Reddit for demand signals, failed attempts, and community sentiment.\n- **Data source**: Reads `[research_folder]/raw/digest/reddit.md` first, falls back to training knowledge\n- **Output**: `[research_folder]/02_reddit_research.md`\n- **Key sections**: Demand Signals, The Graveyard, Pricing Expectations, Retention & Stickiness Signals, Signal Strength\n\n### Stage 1c: Competitive Analysis — `competitive-analyst.md`\nMaps the complete competitive landscape with URLs, pricing, traction, and growth channels.\n- **Data source**: Reads `[research_folder]/raw/digest/brave.md` first, falls back to training knowledge\n- **Output**: `[research_folder]/03_competitive_landscape.md`\n- **Key sections**: Direct Competitors, Big Tech Threat, Market Gaps, How Competitors Grew, How Competitors Retain\n\n### Stage 1d: Market Analysis — `market-analyst.md`\nAnalyzes market size, timing, technology trends, and the 12-month outlook.\n- **Data source**: Training knowledge + `[research_folder]/raw/digest/brave.md` for context\n- **Output**: `[research_folder]/04_market_trends.md`\n- **Key sections**: TAM/SAM/SOM, Why Now, Tailwinds/Headwinds, 12-Month Window\n\n### Stage 1e: Hacker News Research — `hn-researcher.md`\nBuilder community sentiment, Show HN history, and technical feasibility signals.\n- **Data source**: Reads `[research_folder]/raw/digest/hn.md` first, falls back to training knowledge\n- **Output**: `[research_folder]/05_hn_research.md`\n- **Key sections**: Show HN History, Technical Sentiment, The HN Contrarian Take\n\n### Stage 1f: Synthesis — `synthesizer.md`\nCombines all research reports into a single executive brief.\n- **Input**: All files in `research/YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS_slug/`\n- **Output**: `research/YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS_slug/00_research_brief.md`\n- **Key sections**: Executive Summary, Competition, Distribution Opportunity, Retention Assessment, Unit Economics Signal, The Honest Take\n\n### Stages 2-5: Interactive Evaluation — `evaluator.md`\nGuides through exploration, stress-testing, growth & retention mechanics, and execution planning.\n- **Input**: Research brief + screening scores\n- **Output**: Interactive conversation → structured summaries per stage\n- **Stages**:\n  - **Stage 2: Exploration** — Positioning, differentiation, one-sentence pitch, \"why us?\", previous attempts\n  - **Stage 3: Stress Test** — Pressure-test from every angle, find fatal flaws, unit economics, retention assessment\n  - **Stage 4: Growth & Retention** — Distribution loops, retention loops (Hook Model), viral mechanics (uses `frameworks/viral-hooks.yaml` for content hooks), path to 100 users **(most important stage)**\n  - **Stage 5: Execution** — 48hr MVP, kill criteria, first action tomorrow\n\n## Standalone Agents\n\n### Idea Generator — `idea-generator.md`\nReads a dimensional framework YAML and generates a ranked shortlist of product ideas.\n- **Input**: Framework YAML file from `frameworks/`\n- **Output**: Ranked list of ~20 ideas with scoring breakdowns\n- **Key behavior**: Distribution Potential scored at 2x weight in default scoring\n\n### Name Checker — `namecheck.mjs`\nAutomated script that generates product name candidates via LLM and checks domain/trademark availability.\n- **Input**: Pitch file (`--pitch`), idea brief (`--brief`), text description (`--idea`), or explicit names as args\n- **Output**: Domain availability (WHOIS across .com/.dev/.io/.ai/.app) + trademark search links per candidate\n- **Dependencies**: `dotenv`, OpenRouter API (`OPENROUTER_API_KEY` in `.env`), `whois` CLI\n- **Usage**: `node namecheck.mjs --pitch pitches/fosterbot.md --vibe \"orphanage for code\" --count 20`\n- **Modes**: Generate names from product context (LLM) or check specific names only (pass names as args)\n- **Key feature**: `--vibe` steers creative direction (metaphors, themes, tone). Summary ranks candidates by .com availability.\n\n## Trend Pipeline\n\n### Trend Scanner — `trend-scan.mjs`\nAutomated data collection script (not an LLM agent). Scans multiple sources for emerging trend signals.\n- **Input**: `trends/themes.yaml` (scan themes, subreddits, GitHub topics, ProductHunt terms)\n- **Output**: `trends/scans/YYYYMMDD.md` (classified signals) + `YYYYMMDD_MANIFEST.json`\n- **Data sources**: HN Algolia, Brave Web Search (+ site:producthunt.com), GitHub Search API, Twitter/XPOZ, Reddit/XPOZ, Instagram/XPOZ, TikTok/XPOZ (when available)\n- **Dependencies**: Same as intel-gather (`@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` via `xpoz-mcp.mjs`, Brave API, OpenRouter for LLM classification)\n- **Usage**: `node trend-scan.mjs [--themes=trends/themes.yaml] [--output=trends/scans] [--1w] [--skip-xpoz]`\n- **Key behavior**: Classifies each signal by wave lifecycle stage (INFRASTRUCTURE → BUILDER → DEMAND → MAINSTREAM). Tags signals as NEW vs RECURRING by diffing against previous scan. GitHub Search finds fast-growing repos by topic.\n\n### Trend Ideator — `trend-ideator.md`\nInterprets trend scan data, maintains a running theory, and generates ranked product concepts.\n- **Input**: Latest scan from `trends/scans/`, existing `trends/theory.md`, user's `trends/macro.md`\n- **Output**: Updated `trends/theory.md` + `pitches/auto/YYYYMMDD.md` (ranked product concepts)\n- **Key behavior**: Tracks wave stage transitions (EMERGING → ACCELERATING → MAINSTREAM → FADING). Identifies gaps (infrastructure without products, demand without supply). Scores concepts on 6 criteria with Wave Strength and Distribution at 2x weight. Each concept tagged NOW / SOON / WATCH for timing urgency.\n\n### Configuration Files\n- **`trends/themes.yaml`** — Scan themes, target subreddits, GitHub topics, ProductHunt search terms. Edit to steer the scanner.\n- **`trends/macro.md`** — User-maintained macro observations, strategic bets, and signals to watch. The ideator reads this alongside live data.\n- **`trends/theory.md`** — Living document maintained by the ideator. Tracks active waves, gaps, fading signals, and the current thesis. Created on first run.\n\n## Data Flow\n\n```\n═══════════════════════ CONCEPT GENERATION ═══════════════════════\n\n  trends/themes.yaml + trends/macro.md\n       │\n       ▼\n  trend-scan.mjs ──► trends/scans/YYYYMMDD.md        [-1.0 Scan]\n       │\n       ▼\n  trend-ideator.md ──► trends/theory.md (updated)     [-1.1 Ideation]\n       │               pitches/auto/YYYYMMDD.md\n       ▼\n  Human selects concepts ─── OR ─── idea-generator.md [-1.2 Selection]\n       │                              │\n       ▼                              │\n  Blue Ocean Transform ◄─────────────┘                [-1.3 Transform]\n       │   Four Actions Framework\n       │   Noncustomer Analysis\n       ▼\n  Product Pitch ──► pitches/[slug].md                 [-1.4 Pitch]\n       │\n       │  ← ON-RAMP: enter here with any idea\n       │\n═══════════════════════ CONCEPT VALIDATION ═══════════════════════\n       │\n       ▼\n  screener.md ──► research/YYYYMMDD_slug/00_screening.md  [0 Screen]\n       │          + search keywords\n       ▼\n  intel-gather.mjs ──► research/.../raw/digest/*.md       [0.5 Intel]\n       │\n       ├──► twitter.md  reddit.md  hn.md  brave.md\n       │\n       ▼\n  5 research agents (parallel)                            [1 Research]\n       │\n       ├─► 01_twitter  02_reddit  03_competitive\n       │   04_market   05_hn\n       │\n       ▼\n  synthesizer.md ──► 00_research_brief.md                 [1f Synthesis]\n       │\n       ▼\n  evaluator.md ──► Stages 2-5 (interactive)               [2-5 Eval]\n       │\n       ▼\n  idea_brief_[slug].md (in research/YYYYMMDD_slug/)       [Output]\n       │\n       ▼  (if verdict positive)\n  namecheck.mjs ──► domain/trademark availability         [6 Naming]\n       │   5 creative lenses + WHOIS + trademark links\n       ▼\n  User picks name                                         [Done]\n```\n\n## Confidence & Anti-Hallucination\n\nAll research agents follow these rules:\n- Tag findings: `[verified]`, `[likely]`, or `[inferred]`\n- Report **Signal Strength**: STRONG / MODERATE / WEAK / SILENT\n- Never fabricate accounts, URLs, handles, or metrics\n- Report \"limited data found\" rather than inventing specifics\n- Include **Data Freshness** header noting knowledge cutoff\n\n## Key Principle\n\n**Three Pillars: Distribution, Retention, Unit Economics.** Every agent surfaces all three:\n- Screening weights Distribution & Growth AND Retention & Stickiness at 1.5x each\n- Research agents (Twitter, Reddit, Competitive) collect retention signals alongside demand signals\n- Synthesizer outputs Distribution Opportunity, Retention Assessment, and Unit Economics Signal sections\n- Competitive analyst probes how competitors grew AND how they retain\n- Stage 4 (Growth & Retention) walks through the Hook Model and viral mechanics\n- Idea generator scores Distribution Potential at 2x\n- An idea strong on distribution but weak on retention is a leaky bucket — flagged explicitly\n\n## Tend Integration\n\nThis project uses Tend for workflow coordination.\n\n### On Startup\n\n1. Read `.tend/TODO` — propose pending items to the developer and ask what to work on.\n2. Review recent git history for context on what's already been done.\n\n### Emitting State Changes\n\nWhen your work state changes, append a line to `.tend/events`:\n\n```\n<ISO-8601-timestamp> <session-id> <state> <message>\n```\n\nUse `$TEND_SESSION_ID` as the session ID if set, otherwise use `_cli`.\n\nStates: `working`, `done`, `stuck`, `waiting`, `idle`\n\nUse the tend CLI if available:\n```bash\ntend emit working \"<what you're starting>\"\ntend emit done \"<summary of what you completed>\"\ntend emit stuck \"<what you need from the human>\"\ntend emit idle\n```\n\nOr append directly:\n```bash\necho \"$(date +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S) ${TEND_SESSION_ID:-_cli} working <description>\" >> .tend/events\n```\n\n### On Completion\n\n- If there are items in `.tend/TODO`, note the next item but wait for the developer to assign it.\n","cwd":"/Users/possum/Projects/tend/tend-cli"}
